-- document-qa.fl — Document Q&A pipeline
-- Demonstrates: read file, chunked analysis, structured extraction
-- Supports: PDF, DOCX, TXT, MD, CSV, JSON
-- Usage: fluent run examples/document-qa.fl
-- Requires: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY

-- ── Load the document ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
-- Change this path to any local document you want to analyse.
Let report be read file "examples/assets/sample.pdf".

Output "=== Document Q&A Pipeline ===".
Output "".
Output "Document loaded:".
Output report.

-- ── Extract key facts ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@model(temperature: 0, max_tokens: 600, format: json)
Ask claude to "Extract the following fields from this document as JSON: title, author, date, summary (max 3 sentences), key_points (list of up to 5 strings), topics (list of strings)." using document report and call the result metadata.

Output "".
Output "Extracted metadata:".
Output metadata.

-- ── Generate FAQ ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@model(temperature: 0.3, max_tokens: 500)
Ask claude to "Generate 5 frequently asked questions and their answers based on this document." using document report and call the result faq.

Output "".
Output "=== FAQ ===".
Output faq.

-- ── Summarise for executive audience ─────────────────────────────────────────
@model(temperature: 0.2, max_tokens: 250)
Ask anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6 to "Write a 3-sentence executive summary of this document suitable for a CEO who has 30 seconds to read it." using document report and call the result exec_summary.

Output "".
Output "=== Executive Summary ===".
Output exec_summary.

-- ── Risk / concern detection ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
@model(temperature: 0, max_tokens: 300, format: json)
Ask claude to "Identify any risks, concerns, action items, or open questions in this document. Return as JSON with keys: risks (list), action_items (list), open_questions (list)." using document report and call the result risks.

Output "".
Output "=== Risks & Actions ===".
Output risks.
